(3, 'Prof. Yusuf Mahbubul Islam', 'Dean of the School of Engineering, Independent University, Bangladesh', '1629928321.jpg', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">Prof. Yusuf Mahbubul Islam has joined Independent University, Bangladesh (IUB) as the Dean of the School of Engineering, Technology and Sciences (SETS).</span><br></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">Renowned scholar and one of the pioneering educationists in computer science &amp; engineering education and research in Bangladesh, Prof. Yusuf Mahbubul Islam has joined Independent University, Bangladesh (IUB) as the Dean of the School of Engineering, Technology and Sciences (SETS).</span><br style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">Prof. Yusuf Mahbubul Islam served as the Vice Chancellor of Daffodil International University (DIU) from 2015 to 2020. He was the former Professor of Computer Science &amp; Engineering of the same University.</span><br style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">Prof. Islam has 39 years of teaching and research experience with various reputed institutions in Bangladesh, UK, and Malaysia. He also worked as Adjunct Professor at the Open University Malaysia (OUM) from 2011 to 2014. Prof. M. Islam obtained his Ph.D. degree in Design, Manufacturing &amp; Engineering Management from Strathclyde University, Glasgow, UK.</span><br></p>', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:41:50', '2021-08-26 01:52:01'),
(4, 'Mohammad Alauddin', 'Additional Secretary, Chairman SREDA', '1629928335.jpg', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: &quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">Mohammad&nbsp;Alauddin&nbsp;assumed the role of Chairman of&nbsp;the Sustainable and Renewable Energy Development Authority&nbsp;(SREDA),&nbsp;the national nodal agency for the promotion of renewable energy and energy efficiency, in June 2020.</span><br></p>', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin-right: 5px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: kalpurushregular; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; width: auto; float: none; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-family: &quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Mohammad&nbsp;Alauddin&nbsp;assumed the role of Chairman of&nbsp;the Sustainable and Renewable Energy Development Authority&nbsp;(SREDA),&nbsp;the national nodal agency for the promotion of renewable energy and energy efficiency, in June 2020.&nbsp;Prior&nbsp;to his current position, he spent<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font: inherit; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;</span>more than<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font: inherit; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;</span>a decade working in the&nbsp;Ministry of&nbsp;Power, Energy and Mineral Resources.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Alauddin started his carrier in the Bangladesh Civil Service administration cadre in 1991. He served in different ministries&nbsp;as well as&nbsp;in&nbsp;field administration in&nbsp;various capacities.&nbsp;Mr. Alauddin&nbsp;received his B.Sc. Ag. (Honours) degree from the Bangladesh Agricultural University. While in service, he earned Masters&nbsp;in Public Affairs&nbsp;(MPA)&nbsp;with specialization in&nbsp;&nbsp;Governance and Public Policy&nbsp;with high distinction&nbsp;from Civil Service College, Dhaka. He also holds a postgraduate diploma in Development Planning. He taught part- time at the Asian University of Bangladesh and the Civil Service College in Dhaka.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin-right: 5px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: kalpurushregular; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; width: auto; float: none; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-family: &quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">He traveled&nbsp;to&nbsp;many countries in Asia, Europe, Africa,&nbsp;Oceania&nbsp;and North America as part of Delegation from&nbsp;the&nbsp;Government of Bangladesh and presented country papers at a number of seminars and symposiums.&nbsp;He attended professional courses at Meridian College in the United Kingdom, Institute of Public-Private Partnership in the United States, Civil Service College in Singapore, The National University of Malaysia&nbsp;(UKM),&nbsp;Japan International Cooperation Agency in Tokyo, Korea International Cooperation Agency in South Korea, The Asian Institute of Technology in Thailand, and a few other institutions.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin-right: 5px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: kalpurushregular; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; width: auto; float: none; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-family: &quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">A development researcher by passion and a&nbsp;green&nbsp;energy enthusiast, Mr. Alauddin contributes on the topic to various national dailies as well as at the national training and policy workshops.&nbsp;He&nbsp;is married and blessed with one daughter and one son.</span></p>', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:41:50', '2021-08-26 01:52:15'),
(5, 'Prof. Dr. Delwar Hossain', 'Professor of International Relations, University of Dhaka', '1629928370.jpg', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">Delwar Hossain, PhD is Professor of International Relations, University of Dhaka, Bangladesh and concurrently Director, East Asia Center, University of Dhaka.</span><br></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">Delwar Hossain, PhD is Professor of International Relations, University of Dhaka, Bangladesh and concurrently Director, East Asia Center, University of Dhaka. Delwar was the Chair of the Department during 2009-2012. He studied at the University of Dhaka for his Bachelor and Masters programs. Subsequently, Delwar did his second Masters and doctoral study in Japan under the prestigious Asian Development Bank and Monbukagusho scholarships respectively. Delwar has more than 27 years of teaching and research experiences in the broad areas of International Relations. Delwar specializes in international relations theories, foreign policy analysis, global cooperation studies, peace &amp; security issues and conflict and development. Delwar also specializes area studies with specific focus on South, Southeast and East Asia. Delwar serves in public and private academic organizations as a senior member to policy making, faculty recruitment, and research evaluation.</span><br></p>', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:41:50', '2021-08-26 01:52:50'),
(6, 'Syed Monjurul Islam', 'Secretary, Ministry of Health and Family Welfare', '1629928387.jpg', '<p><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Open Sans, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">Syed Monjurul Islam</font><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">, Secretary, Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Government of the People’s Republic of Bangladesh is a career civil servant.</span><br></p>', '<p><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Open Sans, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">Syed Monjurul Islam</font><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">, Secretary, Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Government of the People’s Republic of Bangladesh is a career civil servant. He took over the charge of the Secretary of the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare on 10 November, 2014. Before joining the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare he served as Secretary in Ministry of Shipping.</span><br></p>', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:41:50', '2021-08-26 01:53:07'),
(7, 'Professor Farid Uddin Ahmed', 'Vice-Chancellor of Shahjalal University of Science and Technology', '1629928404.jpg', '<p>Professor Farid Uddin Ahmed is a Bangladeshi academic and the current Vice-Chancellor of Shahjalal University of Science and Technology.<br></p>', '<p>Professor Farid Uddin Ahmed is a Bangladeshi academic and the current Vice-Chancellor of Shahjalal University of Science and Technology. He completed his master\'s degree in economics degree from Monash University. He had served as a professor of the department of economics and the dean of faculty of social sciences at the University of Dhaka.<br></p>', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:41:50', '2021-08-26 01:53:24'),
(8, 'Dr. Salehuddin Ahmed', 'Professor, BRAC University', '1629928424.jpg', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: AvenirLTStd-Roman, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">Dr. Salehuddin Ahmed joined as the Governor of the Bangladesh Bank (Central Bank) on 02 May, 2005 and completed his four year tenure on 30 April 2009.</span><br></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: AvenirLTStd-Roman, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">Dr. Salehuddin Ahmed joined as the Governor of the Bangladesh Bank (Central Bank) on 02 May, 2005 and completed his four year tenure on 30 April 2009. Dr. Salehuddin Ahmed was the Managing Director of Palli Karma-Sahayak Foundation (PKSF), the apex funding agency of microcredit operations in Bangladesh.. He obtained his Ph.D. in Economics from McMaster University, Canada in 1978. He started his career with a short period in the planning Department of the Government of East Pakistan and then joined as a teacher in Economics at Dhaka University and joined the civil service of the government in the erstwhile Civil Service of Pakistan (CSP) cadre. He served in various capacities in field of administration in the Government of Bangladesh. He worked at the Centre on Integrated Rural Development for Asia and the Pacific (CIRDAP), a regional inter-governmental organization with its headquarter in Dhaka. He was the Director General of Bangladesh Academy for Rural Development (BARD) Comilla. He worked as the Director General of the NGO Affairs Bureau under the Office of the Prime Minister. As the Governor of the central bank, he was responsible for formulating monetary policy and its implementation as well as regulating the banks and financial institutions.He has authored more than 80 books, reports and journal articles which have been published at home and abroad.&nbsp; He has worked as a Consultant for international agencies like ADB, APDC, ESCAP, FAO, ILO, UNCRD, UNDP, UNESCO and the World Bank. He is on advisory bodies of several government and non-government agencies in Bangladesh and a member of the Board of Trustees of two universities and a college. As a part-time faculty member, he taught at the Masters’ level at the North South University and the Dhaka University in the year 2009. From January 2010, to 18 January 2014 he was&nbsp;&nbsp; Professor, School of Business, North South University, and Dhaka, Bangladesh and from 26 January 2014 he is Professor in the Business School, BRAC University, and Dhaka, Bangladesh.</span><br></p>', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:41:50', '2021-08-26 01:53:44');

