(3, 'Blended Learning Platform', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#212529; font-family:system-ui,-apple-system,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,Arial,&quot;Noto Sans&quot;,&quot;Liberation Sans&quot;,sans-serif,&quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;,&quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;,&quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;,&quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;\">A blended learning platform is the combination of hardware, software, scheduling, and logistics that make up a learning program that includes online instruction or teaching supplemented with technology.</span></p>', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/bpdb_new/d3pbs_uploads/files/2186_2.jpg\" style=\"width: 535px; height: 300px;\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#212529; font-family:system-ui,-apple-system,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,Arial,&quot;Noto Sans&quot;,&quot;Liberation Sans&quot;,sans-serif,&quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;,&quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;,&quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;,&quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;\">A blended learning platform is the combination of hardware, software, scheduling, and logistics that make up a learning program that includes online instruction or teaching supplemented with technology. Successful implementation of a blended learning platform requires a planned strategy of steps in a particular order. Schools, districts, and networks should start with learning goals and blended models, then decide on platform and content, followed by the selection of devices. In selecting a learning platform, it should have several characteristics that will benefit students and teachers.</span></p>', '20210923_1632387397.png', NULL, 2, '2021-07-05 13:50:26', '2021-11-04 12:54:21'),
