(26, 'Dr. Lutfa Akter', 'dr-lutfa-akter', 2, 'lutfaakter@eee.buet.ac.bd', NULL, '+88 01776 197 537', '20191219_1576730846.jpg', 28, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 14px;\">1. Umma Hany and Lutfa\r\nAkter, \"Non-parametric Approach using ML Estimated Path Loss based WCL for\r\nVideo Capsule Endoscope Localization,\" IEEE Sensors Journal, vol. 18, no.\r\n11, pp. 4761-4769, May, 2018.</span><br><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n2. Lutfa Akter, Neelanjana Subin Ferdous and Zobaer Ahmed, \"Transmit Power\r\nand Bits/Channel Use Adaption in Competitive Cognitive Radio Networks,\"\r\nvol. 24, pp. 123-130, Physical Communication, Elsevier, July 11, 2017.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Lutfa Akter received PhD degree in\r\nElectrical Engineering from Kansas State University, United States of America\r\n(USA) in 2010. She received her BSc and MSc Engineering degrees both on\r\nElectrical and Electronic Engineering (EEE) from Bangladesh University of\r\nEngineering and Technology (BUET) in 2002 and 2004, respectively. She joined\r\nthe Department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering (EEE) of Bangladesh\r\nUniversity of Engineering and Technology (BUET) in 2002 as a lecturer and is\r\ncurrently a Professor in the same department. Her current research interests\r\nare on resource allocation on cognitive radio networks/wireless sensor\r\nnetworks, wireless sensor deployment, antennas and propagation, localization of\r\nwireless video capsule endoscope etc.</span><