Yan\r\nand T. K. Saha, “Investigation of Load Frequency Relief from Field Measurements\r\nand Its Impact on Contingency Reserve Evaluation”, IEEE Transactions on Power\r\nSystems, vol. 33, no. 1, pp. 567-577, 2018.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">2. R. Yan, N. Masood, T. K.\r\nSaha, F. Bai and H. Gu, “The Anatomy of the 2016 South Australia Blackout: A\r\nCatastrophic Event in a High Renewable Network”, IEEE Transactions on Power\r\nSystems, vol. 33, no. 5, pp. 5374 - 5388, 2018.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Power system analysis\r\nand modeling, Power system dynamic response, Transient stability, Grid\r\nintegration of large-scale wind and PV, Power system security, planning,\r\nreliability and asset management, Load and renewable generation forecasting.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Dr. Nahid-Al-Masood\r\ncompleted his B.Sc. and M.Sc. in EEE from BUET, Dhaka, Bangladesh in 2008 and\r\n2010 respectively. He earned the PhD degree in Power and Energy Systems from\r\nThe University of Queensland (UQ), Brisbane, Australia, in 2017. Currently, he\r\nis working as an Associate Professor in the Department of EEE, BUET. He is also\r\nan honorary research fellow in the School of ITEE, UQ. His research interests\r\ninclude power system modeling and analysis, and grid integration of renewable\r\nenergy. He has more than 50 publications in reputed international journals and\r\nconferences. Dr. Masood is a senior member of IEEE.&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL, 'http://nahid.buet.ac.bd', 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=RXAUiVwAAAAJ&hl=en', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-12-18 22:55:30', '2020-02-23 05:26:11'),
(34, 'Dr. Sajid Muhaimin Choudhury', 'dr-sajid-muhaimin-choudhury', 4, 'sajid@eee.buet.ac.bd', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">PhD,&nbsp;Purdue\r\nUniversity, USA, 2019</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">MSc,\r\nBUET, Bangladesh, 2011</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\r\n\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\r\n\r\n</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">BSc,&nbsp;BUET,\r\nBangladesh, 2009</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '+88 01611 978 855', '20191219_1576731491.jpg', 40, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">* Sajid M Choudhury, Di\r\nWang, Krishnakali Chaudhuri, Clayton DeVault, Alexander V Kildishev, Alexandra\r\nBoltasseva, Vladimir M Shalaev, \"Material platforms for optical\r\nmetasurfaces\", Nanophotonics 7 (6), 959-987 (2018)</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">* Sajid Choudhury, Urcan Guler, Amr Shaltout, Vladimir M. Shalaev, Alexander V.\r\nKildishev, Alexandra Boltasseva, \"Pancharatnam–Berry Phase Manipulating\r\nMetasurface for Visible Color Hologram Based on Low Loss Silver Thin\r\nFilm\", Advanced Optical Materials 2017, 5, 1700196.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Amr\r\nShaltout, Sajid Choudhury, Alexander V Kildishev, Alexandra Boltasseva,\r\nVladimir M Shalaev, \"System for producing ultra-thin color phase hologram\r\nwith metasurfaces\", US20160334758 A1, Date: 2018/4/24 Application\r\nDate:2016/5/11, Patent Number:9952557 Application number: 15152535</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Nanophotonics, Metasurface,\r\nMetamaterials, Plasmonics, Numerical Electromagnetics, Open Source EM\r\nSimulation.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Dr.\r\nSajid Choudhury is working as an Assistant Professor in the Department of EEE,\r\nBUET. Dr. Choudhury completed his PhD from the School of Electrical and\r\nComputer Engineering in Purdue University. Dr. Choudhury had the privilege of\r\nacquiring skills of both experimental and numerical approaches to solve\r\nproblems related to photonics. His&nbsp; goal\r\nis to establish an independent research career in Bangladesh with\r\nmultidisciplinary collaborations to attack problems related to food safety,\r\nenergy, healthcare and communications. Dr. Choudhury is a member of the IEEE\r\nand OSA. For more details, please visit his personal website: sajid.buet.ac.bd</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'ECE 331', 'http://sajid.buet.ac.bd', 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=Fu8Hkb4AAAAJ&hl=en', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-12-18 22:58:12', '2020-08-17 03:06:48'),
(35, 'Dr. Ahmed Zubair', 'dr-ahmed-zubair', 4, 'ahmedzubair@eee.buet.ac.bd', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">PhD,&nbsp;Rice\r\nUniversity, USA, 2017</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">MSc,&nbsp;BUET,\r\nBangladesh, 2011</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">BSc,&nbsp;BUET,\r\nBangladesh, 2009</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '+88 01300 574 069', '20191219_1576731597.jpg', 41, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">1. NEXT Research Grant\r\nAward, CEMES, CNRS, France 2. Best Technology Award, 2014 GMSI-GSDM Summer\r\nCamp, University of Tokyo.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">1.\r\nA. Zubair, D. E. Tsentalovich, C. C. Young, M. S. Heimbeck, H. O. Everitt, M.\r\nPasquali, and J. Kono, “Carbon nanotube fiber terahertz polarizer,” Applied\r\nPhysics Letters, vol. 108, no. 14, p. 141107, 2016.&nbsp; 2. A. Zubair, X. Wang, F. Mirri, D. E.\r\nTsentalovich, N. Fujimura, D. Suzuki, K. P. Soundarapandian, Y. Kawano, M.\r\nPasquali, and J. Kono, “Carbon nanotube woven textile photodetector,” Phys.\r\nRev. Materials, vol. 2, p. 015201, 2018.</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">﻿</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Nanoengineering,\r\nNanophotonics, Optoelectronics, Terahertz Technology, Sustainable Energy.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Dr.\r\nAhmed Zubair received his B.S. and M.S. degrees in Electrical and Electronic\r\nEngineering from the Bangladesh University of Engineering and Technology (BUET)\r\nin 2009 and 2011, respectively, and completed his Ph.D. in Electrical and\r\nComputer Engineering from the Rice University, Houston, Texas, USA in 2017.\r\nAhmed Zubair is currently an Assistant Professor in Electrical and Electronic\r\nEngineering at BUET. He is a Member of Optical Society (OSA), American Physical\r\nSociety (APS), Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE),\r\nAmerican Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS), and Materials\r\nResearch Society (MRS).</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'ECE 913', 'http://ahmedzubair.buet.ac.bd', 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=_df3TicAAAAJ&hl=en', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-12-18 22:59:57', '2020-08-17 03:07:19'),
(36, 'Dr. Md. Asiful Islam', 'dr-md-asiful-islam', 4, 'maislam@eee.buet.ac.bd', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">PhD,&nbsp;The\r\nOhio State University,&nbsp;USA, 2017</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">MSc,\r\nBUET, Bangladesh, 2013</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\r\n\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\r\n\r\n</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">BSc,&nbsp;BUET,\r\nBangladesh, 2009</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '+88 01906 200 154', '20191219_1576731786.jpg', 42, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">1. M A Islam, A Kiourti and JL Volakis, \"A novel method to mitigate real-imaginary\r\nimage imbalance in microwave tomography,\" IEEE Trans on Biomed. Engg, Aug.\r\n2019. [2] M A Islam and M S Alam, \"An extremely large mode area\r\nmicrostructured core leakage channel fiber with low bending loss,\" Journal\r\nof Lightwave Technology, 2013.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL, '<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\">Microwave Imaging, Antennas for biological Media, Photonic Waveguides\r\nand Fibers</span><br></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Dr. Md Asiful Islam\r\nreceived his B.S. and M.S. degrees in Electrical and Electronic Engineering\r\nfrom the Bangladesh University of Engineering and Technology (BUET) in 2009 and\r\n2013, respectively, and completed his Ph.D. in Electrical and Computer\r\nEngineering from The Ohio State University, Columbus, OH, USA in 2017. He is\r\ncurrently an Assistant Professor in Electrical and Electronic Engineering at\r\nBUET. During PhD he worked in the Electroscience Laboratory of OSU, a pioneer\r\nin the Electromagnetics and Antenna research in the world. Md Asiful Islam\'s\r\nresearch interest are in the areas of Microwave Imaging, Antennas for\r\nbiological media and Photonic Waveguides and Fibers. He has authored more than\r\n20 articles in peer reviewed journals and conferences.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'ECE 131', 'http://maislam.buet.ac.bd', 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=QyGpYmwAAAAJ&hl=en', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-12-18 23:03:06', '2020-08-17 03:08:19'),
